<p n="4-9">
                        
<supplied reason="subaudible">This is</supplied> the stone 
<supplied reason="subaudible">of</supplied> Kākaṇṭi Aṇṇāvaṉ, the servant of Poṉṉarampaṉār, he who fell recapturing 
<supplied reason="explanation">
  <foreign>iṭuvittu</foreign>
  <note>That is (?), 
  <foreign>viṭuvittu</foreign>, literally "liberating".</note>
</supplied> cattle when Kantaviṇṇaṉār, the nephew of the royal Bāṇa king seized cattle 
<supplied reason="subaudible">in</supplied> kūṭal.        
                </p>
                
                
<p n="10-12">
                        
<supplied reason="subaudible">This is</supplied> stone that the 
